1Ô∏è‚É£ What is AWS Snow Family?
AWS Snow Family = Set of offline, rugged physical devices used to migrate large datasets into or out of AWS when:
Internet is slow, unreliable, or non-existent
Environment is remote / edge / non-data center
Need local compute + storage for edge processing

Members:
AWS Snowcone ‚Äì smallest, portable
AWS Snowball ‚Äì mid-size (Edge Storage / Edge Compute)
AWS Snowmobile ‚Äì 45-foot shipping container for exabytes

Used to:
Move TB ‚Üí PB ‚Üí EB of data
Run edge computing workloads (IoT, ML inference, preprocessing)
Deploy local EC2 + IoT Greengrass

2Ô∏è‚É£ Standard Features of AWS Snow Family
‚úî 1. Encryption (Automatic + Strong)
All data is encrypted with AES-256.

Keys managed by AWS KMS.
Keys never stored on device ‚Üí secure even if stolen.

Exam Tip:
"If a Snow device is lost or stolen during transit, is customer data safe?"
YES ‚Üí encryption + TPM + auto wipe.

‚úî 2. On-board Computing
Devices can run:
EC2 instances
AWS IoT Greengrass
Local data filtering, preprocessing & compression

Useful for:
Remote locations (ships, oil rigs)
Military field data
Factory edge ML

‚úî 3. End-to-End Tracking
E-ink shipping label (auto updates)
SNS notifications
Track using AWS Console

‚úî 4. Anti-Tamper / Tamper Evident
Trusted Platform Module (TPM)
Hardware root of trust
Device re-initialized after each use

‚úî 5. NFS Endpoint
Snow devices support:
NFS v3 & v4.1

Use case:
Mount device like a normal file share
Copy data from on-prem servers easily

‚úî 6. Simple Management (AWS OpsHub GUI)
AWS OpsHub helps you:
Unlock / configure device
Launch EC2 instances on the device
Transfer files
Monitor data migration

‚úî 7. Secure Erasure (NIST Wipe)
After migration:
AWS performs software erasure
Follows NIST 800-88 media sanitization standard

Ensures:
No customer data remains on device

3Ô∏è‚É£ Snow Family Members (Deep Dive)
üü¶ 1. AWS Snowcone
Smallest device
Portable, works on battery or AC
Sensors, drones, vehicles, remote sensors
Specs:
8 TB storage
2 vCPU + 4 GB RAM (Edge compute version)

Use Cases:
Disaster zones
Remote IoT data capture
Drone video offloading

üü© 2. AWS Snowball (Edge Storage / Edge Compute)
Two types:
Snowball Edge Storage Optimized
80 TB usable storage
Ideal for large migrations
Snowball Edge Compute Optimized
More CPU, GPU options
Run ML inference, analytics

Use Cases:
Migrate hundreds of TB
Local compute in remote locations
Build local mini-cloud environments

üü• 3. AWS Snowmobile
Literally a truck (45-foot container)
Moves up to 100 PB per Snowmobile
Designed for exabyte-scale migrations
Use Case:
Data center exit
Media archives
Government / satellite imagery

4Ô∏è‚É£ Example Story to Remember Easily
üí° Imagine you run an exploration team in the Himalayas‚Ä¶
The team needs to store data with no internet ‚Üí Snowcone
Base camp wants to run ML inferencing locally ‚Üí Snowball Compute Optimized
After expedition ends, the company must migrate 10 PB archive ‚Üí Snowmobile

5Ô∏è‚É£ Important Points for Exam
Topic	Exam-Level Knowledge
Encryption	AES-256, KMS managed, no keys on device
Data loss risk	Safe ‚Üí device is encrypted + TPM
Migration size	TB ‚Üí Snowcone, 80TB+ ‚Üí Snowball, 100PB+ ‚Üí Snowmobile
Compute support	EC2 + Greengrass on Snowcone/Snowball
Tracking	E-ink label + SNS
Sanitization	NIST-800-88 wipe

Typical Question:
Which Snow device to choose when migrating 50 PB of data?
üëâ Snowmobile

6Ô∏è‚É£ Quick Summary (for last-minute revision)
Snow Family = offline physical devices for data migration + edge compute
Members: Snowcone, Snowball, Snowmobile
Features: AES-256 encryption, TPM security, NFS support, OpsHub GUI, NIST wipe
Snowcone = portable small data collection
Snowball = medium data + edge compute
Snowmobile = exabyte-scale migration

AWS Snow Family ‚Äì MCQs (35 Questions)
